==English==
===Etymology===
Latin [[allusio]], fr. alludere to allude: compare with French [[allusion]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈlu.ʒən/

===Noun===
# A reference to something supposed to be known, but not explicitly mentioned; a covert indication; indirect reference; a hint.
